                    <p class="blog-para">
                    Recently Johnson & Johnson was ordered to pay $72M of damages to the family of a woman whose death from ovarian cancer was linked to their use of the company’s talc-based Baby Powder, reported by NBC News. Although this is not the only case of personal products company being called out for using harmful ingredients as there have been several instances that organizations selling beauty products were subjected to review their goods based on detrimental elements usage. In fact, with many noxious ingredients found in beauty products, it is uncanny how women pay attention to what to buy from the market as after all skin is the largest organ of the body.

<p class="break">More than that the artificial scents used to cover the odor of chemicals in synthetic products can create congestion, headaches, and nasal irritation as we are capable of absorbing up to 60% of the ingredients found in skincare products. That may eventually lead to life-lasting skin-damaging effects such as skin cancer or even death.</p>



<p class="break">The good news is that many organic products are emerging in the market and is good for people allergic to certain skin lightening chemicals. While some brands have been able to spot and bank on the organic variety available, consumers are becoming more interested to know the importance of using chemical-free products with the right ingredients for their bodies. Organic products are gaining more popularity due to the awareness of healthy skin without the detrimental after-effects on the body in the long run on their overall wellbeing.</p>



<p class="break">In most cases, women are more interested in the advantage of using natural organic skincare products to enhance their natural skin condition in synergy with the good lightning effects by utilizing natural active ingredients that may improve overall skin restoration. Recently, market analysts predict that the market for organic cosmetics and natural organic cosmetics will grow in the coming years due to their promising dermatological rewards. Organic and natural skin care products can bring about better improvement in persistent skin concerns such as psoriasis, edma, acne, premature aging, dryness, hyper-pigmentation or sensitized skin. Moreover, organic skincare products are free of harmful skincare ingredients, artificial dyes, synthetic fillers, and harsh chemicals that cause wrinkling, irritation, dryness, redness, and wear out of the skin.</p>

<h3 class="heading__para">VALUE FOR MONEY</h3>

<p class="break">It is a misconception that organic skincare and lightening products are pricier than the mainstream products, although this is not true in any case. Estee Lauder, Lancome, Chanel is already leading the market with their high-end beauty products and surely organic creams are not as dirt-cheap as mass-produced chemical supermarket brands. Think of it like this: junk food is way cheaper than organic food, but wouldn’t you rather spend £1 on a few organic bananas instead of a huge bad of free radical laden, salty, MSG riddled cirps? Better for you, and the same price! One of the many organic brands in the market is growing with their natural lightening products know as https://bodycontours.org/  you can find out more on their website.</p>



    <p class="break">So why should we use organic skincare for the first place? The answer is pretty obvious by now and that is organic products are healthier at reasonable prices and only include ingredients that will nourish your skin and body and also it is very important to only put high-quality organic creams on your delicate skin as your skin deserves to healthy and shining. Find out more products such as lightening body lotion on https://bodycontours.org/</p>
